    "rationale": "This example demonstrates the oxidation of a sterically hindered secondary alcohol (1-cyclohexyl-2,2-dimethyl-1-propanol) to the corresponding ketone (1-cyclohexyl-2,2-dimethyl-1-propanone) under Swern conditions. The presence of the bulky tert-butyl and cyclohexyl groups makes this transformation specific and less likely to be a generic oxidation example, while clearly illustrating the core alcohol-to-carbonyl conversion of the Swern oxidation.",
    "collision_avoidance_note": "The substrate contains both a cyclohexyl and a tert-butyl group attached to the carbinol carbon, creating a distinct and sterically demanding environment. This specific substitution pattern is chosen to avoid overlap with simpler, more common alcohol oxidation examples (like cyclohexanol or simple aliphatic alcohols) and to provide a unique structural fingerprint for this reaction family.",
